{
  "text": "Health information exchange (HIE) becomes more and more important in medical services within the exchange of information among heterogeneous systems in medical institutions and regions. The sharing of clinical information could not only facilitate clinic visit, lower medical costs, and maximize the use of limited resources, but also assure the consistency and accessibility of clinical data to make a patient centered service, by which doctors could fast read the important clinical information such as medical and allergic history, to assure the safety and continuity of treatment, reduce human errors, and enhance the entire service qualities of medical industries [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
  "correct_citation": {
